title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ P01+Kadet .22 Conversion+ Crimson Trace, Night Sights, Lots of mags/ holsters
postcontent:
I have a CZ P01 for sale or trade. Used but not abused. It comes with the standard P01 9mm upper with Meprolight Night Sights, and the CZ .22 Kadet conversion kit. The P01 frame wears Crimson Trace model LG-476. This package includes the following:
-CZ-P01 + 2 14 Rnd. CZ factory mags
-Kadet .22 Conversion Kit + 2 .22 10 Rnd. CZ factory mags (Be aware the Kadet conversion was made for the full size frame of the CZ-75, not the compact. The dust cover does not go all the way to the muzzle, and the .22 magazine caps stick out. You can see this in the Photo. This does not effect overall function of the firearm in any way.)
-Crimson Trace model LG-476 grips installed
-Meprolight TRU-DOT Night Sight system for CZ-75 Compact
-Factory CZ compact rubber grips
-2 32 Round 9mm "fun stick" mags. (one is a promag, the other is not labeled. They are fun, but grumpy when you put more than 28-30 rounds in them)
-Unlabeled Kydex OWB holster. (fits fantastically)
-Modified USP compact Blackhawk Serpa holster (fits fantastically)
-CZ factory mag loader.
-Original CZ factory P01 combat sights
-All original paperwork

This is one of the most fantastic guns I have ever owned. I have never had a FTF, or FTE, and this little beauty ingests anything you put through it. It is astonishingly accurate, both 9mm, and .22 uppers, and is the most comfortable handling and holding pistol on the market IMHO. If you don't know anything about CZ 75 pistols, do yourself a favor and look them up. If you can go out and shoot one. The P-01 is based on the CZ 75, the most used pistol in the world. The P01 was put through some of the most rigorous small arms testing ever. It was adopted by the Czech national police. It is a NATO classified pistol and issued the NATO stock number NSN 1005-16-000-8619. A description of the NATO certification trials can be found on CZ's website. http://cz-usa.com/press-release/cz-p-01-gets-nato-approval-the-next-generation-of-perfect-pistols/

This is a package deal including everything listed above. I am looking for $775.00 OBO, or trade for a good deer rifle. I am particular to Rem. 700 BDL, or a higher end Savage. I like Combo's and I like Nikon. Otherwise I am up for any trade that fits my needs. ID, firearms purchase certificate, bill of sale, and a good demeanor required for sale or trade.

postcontent:
Up for grabs is a M4 Carbine. This is not your typical consumer grade M4/AR15 platform or accessories. It meets/exceeds Military specifications all the way around, using only high end parts and components as you are about to see.

I present the Daniel Defense DDM4 V5 M4 Carbine Mil-Spec Rifle. Below is a link giving the specifics of this same rifle for sale (except the stock). The rifle is 100% factory installed, not a "parts gun". Daniel Defense is widely considered the premier MIL SPEC AR15/M4 platforms being made. It is one sexy and effective piece of art...

https://danieldefense.com/firearms/mid-length/daniel-defense-m4-carbine-v5.html

I purchased and added on to this rifle after doing many months of research on creating the "perfect weapon system" for any defensive/offensive situation in virtually any scenario that would come up. ONLY reason I am selling is because I am saving up for a full auto, so my baby has to go...

As part of building this weapon system, I chose the:

-Daniel Defense M4 Carbine because it kept popping up in list after list of the "best of the best" because of its durability, attention to detail/quality, and adherence to Military Specifications/tolerances. Watch this video on YouTube and you'll see why the DDM4 is the best M4/AR15 on the market from a durability standpoint http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y1kX0nCEh5E

-Burris MTAC Ballistic CQ/LR (Close Quarter/Long Range) tactical optic because it offers both Close Quarters and Medium/Long Range capabilities in the same platform and the same time. Using "true 1x" it allows for both eyes open use (just like a red dot...AimPoint for example), and up to 4x magnification with built in 5.56 BDC reticles for effective engagements up to 600 yards. Just zero for 100 yards (which it already is) and your ready to go out to 600 yards using the built in BDC dots. It is extremely clear, has illuminated reticle (which work even if the battery dies), weather and shock proof, with a lifetime warranty. It is just like having both a Red Dot and a Tactical magnified scope in one, giving you the best of both worlds in one small, lightweight package.

-5.11 LED Tactical Lightweight High Output Weapons light because of it's superior performance inside of an extremely light frame. It is weather/shock proof with high, low, and strobe capabilities. Mounts perfect along side the foregrip for easy of use in any conditions.

-45 degree backup sight for obvious reasons; just in case something were to happen the MTAC optic this rifle can still be effective at close and medium/long ranges.

-Viking VTAC battle sling after much research in the best sling for all situations. Check out how awesome this sling is here: 
http://www.vikingtactics.com/product-p/vtac-mk2.htm

-Quick detach Harris bipod. Small and compact, but adjustable and sturdy. Can be added/removed to the M4 very quickly if the situation requires it. Quickly turns this M4 from a close quarters machine into a medium/long tactical precision weapon. 

Comes with everything listed above, plus:

Hard Carrying case, (4) 30 round mags, 90 rounds of ammo, scope lenses covers, and original boxes for most accessories.

I have well over $2500 invested in this barely used and meticulously cleaned package. Cash price is $2100 OBO. This is extremely fair for everything included...you will NOT regret taking this beauty home. Please be realistic with your offers or they will be ignored.

FTF only, no shipping. Must be 18 with an OHIO ID. CCW preferred (I'll show you mine as well). 

I have extra mags and ammo for purchase to buyer ONLY.

postcontent:
The P-3AT is a semi-automatic, locked breech pistol, chambered for the .380 Auto cartridge. It has been developed from our highly successful P-32 pistol with negligible increase in weight and size. The slidestop has been eliminated and the magazine capacity reduced to 6 rounds due to the larger cartridge. The firing mechanism is double action only. The magazine has a 6 round capacity. The KEL-TEC P-3AT is the lightest .380 Auto pistol ever made. Thanks to its locking dynamics and superior ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-3AT is mainly intended for plainclothes police officers as a secondary weapon, or for concealed carry by licensed citizens. The small grip size and light trigger pull make the P-3AT ideal for female shooters.


The P-3AT has five main component groups: barrel, slide, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 ordnance steel, heat treated to 48 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. After firing, the hammer block holds the hammer away from the firing pin, providing a mechanical safety.

You get one 1/2 lb Tannerite target. Tannerite® Brand Binary Exploding Targets are a binary explosive used primarily as a shot indicator for firearms practice. Tannerite® is unique in that it is exceptionally stable when subjected to less severe forces such as a hammer blow or being dropped. It is more than 1,000 times safer than ordinary black powder since it is not flammable and can not be initiated by any kind of flame or electricity. It is supplied as two powders which are combined to produce the explosive. Tannerite® is a trademarked name, and binary exploding targets are a patented invention by Daniel J. Tanner/Oregon. Tannerite® detonations occur at a very high velocity, producing a large explosion and cloud of water vapor. It may be useful for persons who are firing at long ranges; in this scenario, a long-range rifle shooter places targets downrange, retreats to his firing position, and fires. The shooter does not have to walk down range to see if he has a hit, the Tannerite® brand target will detonate and serve as an indicator. Since the two components are not explosive until mixed, they can legally be purchased in the USA without a license. They can be legally used for sporting purposes in conjunction with small arms, just like black powder and other exempt sporting powder. The federal government, not the state, governs the manufacture of explosives. They specifically exempt the need for an explosives manufacturing license in five separate statutes. In the CFR (Code of Federal Regulations) Publication 5400. Q&A section, question #48 expressly addresses that a license is not needed for personal, non-commercial manufacture and use of binary explosives.
